<Author>bbohannon
<Content>The Pelham The Pelham Hotel is what you think of when you think New Orleans Style. It's probably the place where Maverick stayed, when he arrived on a riverboat, after a long gambling river cruise, a century ago.The Pelham relaxes in a refurbished, yet old-fashioned New Orleans charm. And, the staff know what Southern Hospitality really means.The location couldn't be better. The Pelham is two blocks from the casino, a block off Canal Street, and a comfortable two blocks from the hystirical French Quarter.Darlene, behind the front desk, as well as all the staff, are very attentive and knowledgeable. The manager, Ronnell Williams, is always there if you need him.There's a restaurant downstairs that serves breakfast all day (something that you'll find to be very important in New Orleans). And, there's vallet parking, although I strongly recommend NOT bringing or renting a car while you're in the Crecent City, as the Po Po (police) work overtime giving tickets to foreigners.I stayed at one of the big, expensive hotels my first few nights in New Orleans, and I honestly found the room at The Pelham to be better (and QUIETER).Why am I telling you all this? I've found a real treasure in the heart of New Orleans, and I should keep it to myself. But, what does it matter? You'll probably just stay at one of the big chain hotels, anyway. And then, you'll always wonder why everybody raves about the charm and warmth of New Orleans.Try the Pelham. 
