<Author>D.C.FamilyTraveler
<Content>A little Gem! Our family of five, including three teenagers was looking for a smaller, quiet hotel just off of the tourist track. Since we needed two rooms, we wanted something nice, but afforable. The Pelham is a gem! Just off mainstream Canal Street and a short walk to the French Quarter and the river front, it is a European type, upscale hotel with excellent service. The rooms are gorgeous, with high ceilings, large white moldings, floor to ceiling windows, luxurous drapes, and a large bathroom. Recently rennovated and redocorated, the rooms, lobby, and halls are classically tasteful and elegant. This is not a standardized concrete box hotel -- the rooms are all different shapes and sizes. Rosies Diner next door had great specials and generous servings -- the meat loaf was terrific. Ronnel Williams, Guest Sevices Manager at the Pelham, was exteremely helpful, outgoing, and friendly, as were all of the staff. He loves his hotel and treats you as his very own guest. All of this for only $85 bucks a room! Don't be fooled by some of the buildings near the Pelham. A few are still being repaired and some are just old, but the location is excellent. A Marriott, other large hotels, the museum, casino, and fine shopping are also just a block two away. Don't miss this one. 
