<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>SOME SUGGESTIONS FOR A PLEASANT STAY The Pelham isn't nearly as horrific as the reviews here; however, there are some things to be aware of:1) Location: This hotel is located near most every attraction one can visit and is perfect for a long weekend stay. Harrah's is two blocks, Canal Street is one block (thus very near the French Quarter) and the Riverwalk and Canal Shops are about 3 blocks. It's a hotel perfect without a car (I rented a vehcile and used it once in three days to drive out to the Garden District). Be wary though as it is located two doors from a Soup Kitch (as is the much more expensive Best Western across the street). New Orleans has a large homeless population, so you probably won't get away from it at any downtown hotel.2) Hotel Staff: I had a very pleasant experience with the front desk staff at the hotel. Not only were they professional when necessary but they new we came for a good time and offered suggestions on food and things to see we wouldn't have ventured to without the suggestions. HOWEVER - in the three nights I was at the hotel, housekeeping never cleaned the room. They came by Saturday morning at about 8AM and I requested they return in shortly as I was still dressing. No return. Sunday, no housekeeping.3) Cautionary advise: The Pelham is currently available for $69.00 per night on the internet. This excludes approximately $7.00USD in vault and long distance charges but they advised me at check in to make sure I was aware of the additional fee. This also excludes parking. Valet parking is available at the hotel for $17.95 per day with in and out priveleges. This isn't a bad price for valet service as many other places charge $25.00 for 24 hours no in and out. Also, the internet specials available, such as the Vodoo Bonus Package and the $20.00 per day voucher require you to print the page or request same when making your reservation. I lucked out and had my laptop to get online and get the page with the specials on it. Use the $20.00 voucher at several restaurants. I recommend The Lafayette Sports Bar as they had good burgers ranginging from $6.00 - 8.00 (nearly enough in the voucher to feed 3 people a day and plenty for 2. Huey's 24/7 next door has a few very rude members of staff and only so so food. The prices are weighted.4) Rooms: The rooms of the hotel are spaces and mostly comfortable but not four star quality. The glass in one panel of our bathrrom window was taped in precariously and the chair at the desk was splitting a bit and probably soon to fall. Also be advised that the bathrooms have only light curtains in them and a large window that can (depending on your room number) face another hotel. People can see in your room easily at night and you can see out (could be good, could be bad depending on your likes). Hang a couple of towels over the bathroom window for more privacy.Overall we had a most pleasant stay at the Pelham (the time we were actually in the room). 
