<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Organization  The Pelham Hotel, May 9-13, 2004You have heard, if you can not say something nice then do not say anything at all! Okay, the Pelham staff is very friendly and courteous! With that said now we can continue with the other items of our review during our stay for which we were the administrators of three meetings with 35 people arriving from all over the United States.Meetings must be organized and are planned per contract with the hotel months in advance. You would not expect,1.The meeting room to be musty and moldy when entering the room, we were expected, Yes!2.The furniture to have an eighth of an inch of dust on the chairs and the table cloths soiled.3.For the meeting room not be prepared until the last minute.4.For refreshments not to be ready as contracted. You should not have to ask for plates and silver ware. Desert dishes not available and neither was the desert until we asked. 5.The meeting room for our events not to be published in the lobby and our agenda鈥檚 were incorrect from information given to us by the hotel. Cleanliness of the rooms and unexpected functionality was an understatement as follows:1.The third floor was in the process of being painted, therefore you had to tolerate the unhealthy smell of paint fumes, paint buckets, and drop cloths in the hallways.2.For fun in the mornings, see how many aunts you can count on the bathroom floor. What an unexpected recreational event, but not as good as games on your laptop however the Internet connection was not working!3.How about a reality show instead? Walk into the room and have the air conditioning until fall from the ceiling and miss your body by inches.4.Wade the water saturated carpet from the bed to the bathroom in several rooms. Now this is taking cleanliness seriously!5.Sure we all have had to request additional towels and/or coffee from housekeeping, but we did not expect to wait two days nor be told by the staff they would check for availability.6.Normally a hotel room is cleaned on a daily basis unless you leave your privacy indicator on the door, not the case at this hotel. Even if the room was cleaned, the same removable soil on the carpet remained for the entire stay. Wonder what kind of vacuum cleaner they use?7.Television does not work! Well, what did you expect? One ice machine which works some of the time and the vending machine was out of order.8.Toilet clogged and the maintenance staff needs assistance. How difficult can it be to use a plunger? Once unclogged, towels are used to clean up the spills in the floor.9.Blankets are obviously soiled and housekeeping does not replace.Suggestion: Do not wear white gloves to this hotel!  
